abstract: The Fed leaves its benchmark interest rate steady, but it signaled that an increase was likely at its next policy meeting in March.
snippet: The Fed leaves its benchmark interest rate steady, but it signaled that an increase was likely at its next policy meeting in March.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve said on Wednesday that it was still trying to stimulate faster economic growth as one of the longest expansions in American history neared the end of its ninth year.

abstract: A consortium announced that it had taken a 55 percent stake in the financial and risk division in a deal that values the unit at $20 billion, including debt.

lead_paragraph: LONDON — What is now Thomson Reuters came to life a decade ago in a $17 billion merger of the Thomson financial information business and the Reuters news service.

abstract: In 1967, David Santiago was forced out of his Lower East Side tenement to make way for urban development, with promises he could return. Now, he has.
snippet: In 1967, David Santiago was forced out of his Lower East Side tenement to make way for urban development, with promises he could return. Now, he has.
lead_paragraph: In 1967, 6-year-old David Santiago and his family were forced out of their tenement apartment on Delancey Street on the Lower East Side of Manhattan to make way for what was supposed to be a massive urban renewal project. At the time, they were promised when the new buildings were finished they would be able to return.

abstract: White House correspondents have plenty of material — and plenty of angst — as they cover what Stephen K. Bannon calls “the first McLuhanesque presidency.”
snippet: White House correspondents have plenty of material — and plenty of angst — as they cover what Stephen K. Bannon calls “the first McLuhanesque presidency.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Asked to reflect on the relationship between President Trump and the news media — an abusive yet symbiotic union, if there ever was one — Stephen K. Bannon, the former White House chief strategist, paused a moment to consider.
